I think you can fix valgrind's issue initializing the `total_effective_amount`:

```diff
diff --git a/src/wallet/spend.h b/src/wallet/spend.h
--- a/src/wallet/spend.h
+++ b/src/wallet/spend.h
@@ -69,7 +69,7 @@
     /** Sum of all available coins raw value */
     CAmount total_amount{0};
     /** Sum of all available coins effective value (each output value minus fees required to spend it) */
-    std::optional<CAmount> total_effective_amount;
+    std::optional<CAmount> total_effective_amount{std::nullopt};
 };
 
 struct CoinFilterParams {
```
(this is a guess but worth to try it)

> I'd be surprised if this worked around the issue. It is triggered in an GCC -O2 pass, so it seems more involved. This false-positive should be properly reduced and reported upstream. However, this is going to take some time (not even considering the time for the upstream fix to propagate). I am happy to take care of this, but I don't think it makes sense to block pull requests based on unrelated upstream bugs. I'd say the task should be (temporarily?) removed, see https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34492 for now.

I wouldn't argue against removing it, but also wouldn't argue against people who want to keep it.
Just thinking that there might be a workaround that doesn't involve much code so everyone is happy and we can upstream this bug without any rush. E.g..
```
if (coin_selection_params.m_subtract_fee_outputs) {
    available_coins_total_amount = available_coins.GetTotalAmount();
} else if (auto op_eff_amount = available_coins.GetEffectiveTotalAmount(); op_eff_amount.has_value()) {
    available_coins_total_amount = *op_eff_amount;
}
```

sorry I actually tried a variation of furszy's suggestion which didn't work.
but thanks! would be nice to use a 1-liner.

- this variation failed on valgrind - so optional + value_or wasn't the problem.
```
  CAmount available_coins_total_amount = 0;
    if (auto total = available_coins.GetAppropriateTotal(coin_selection_params.m_subtract_fee_outputs); total.has_value()) {
        available_coins_total_amount = *total;
    }
```
- apparently optional + ternary was the problem for valgrind. (tried this on my personal fork and it worked)
```
    std::optional<CAmount> GetAppropriateTotal(bool subtract_fee_outputs) const {
        if (subtract_fee_outputs) {
            std::optional<CAmount> result = total_amount;
            return result;
        } else {
            std::optional<CAmount> result = total_effective_amount;
            return result;
        }
    }
```

